parameters: Neneko enters the makeshift throne room by Anzu's side.\.\. The cat makes no attempt to seem like she wants to be there.\.\. Anzu meanwhile walks as if she owns the place.\.\.
Before they reach Ruina,\. however,\. the same guard from before blocks the way.\.\.
\n<Dwarf Axeman>Halt!\.\. While the Queen has allowed you entry,\. Beast,\. you were not told you could bring another!\.\.
\n<Ruina>That is enough.\.\. Let them through.\.\. That is an important guest.\.\.
Neneko isn't sure if she just heard the stoic dwarf sigh just now.\.\.
The overzealous guard bows her head and then retreats back to her normal position.\.\. Anzu gives a haughty huff before stepping forward.\.\.
Neneko rolls her eyes and keeps pace.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>To you as well,\. Queen Ruina.\.\. I do apologize for not sending prior notice of my visit.\.\. \BST[7]There have been a few complications above ground,\. you see.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Complications,\. that's one way to put it...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Is that so?\.\. That would explain the lack of correspondence from your Manor for the last few months,\. I suppose.\.\.
\n<Ruina>It's of no consequence.\.\. You are here already,\. after all.\.\. I very well cannot turn you away.\.\.
Although Neneko gets the feeling if she had an excuse to do so it wouldn't be too big of a loss to her...\.\.\.
Looks like these two have a strictly business relationship.\.\.
\n<Ruina>I will admit I am surprised you two are acquainted,\. however.\.\.
Anzu smiles confidently,\. waving her hand.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>She is simply a stray cat who has caught my attention and affections and I have decided to take under my wing for a while~\.
\n<\n[5]>She's rough around the edges and rude but very much capable,\. you see.\.\.
The dwarf peers at Neneko,\. enough to make the cat cough awkwardly.\.\.
\n<Ruina>It's your own decision.\.\. \BST[5]Far be it from me to question your choice in company.\.\.
Ruina straightens up,\. locking eyes with Anzu.\.\.
\n<Ruina>But we are moving away from the important topics.\.\. Leaving your post aboveground to come to the First Stratum.\.\. You would not come down here without prior notice on a simple visit.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Yes yes,\. don't be so tense.\.\. Simply put,\. I must have a meeting with my superiors over certain issues that have come to my attention above ground.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>To that end,\. I require access to the Caldera Lift to take me below.\.\.
\n<Ruina>I am afraid there is a problem with that.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Guess they don't want a bat problem,\. heh...\.\.\.
She turns to pout at Neneko,\. before looking back to Ruina,\. frowning.\.\. Before she can start questioning/whining,\. Ruina raises a hand,\. asking for patience.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Do not misunderstand.\.\. I have no reason to refuse you access,\. and indeed I would have someone escort you to the Lift if I could...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>But we have a situation ourselves here.\.\. There is currently no access to the Lift at this time.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Wh-\.what?\.\. How could that be?\.\. \BST[2]Ugh.\.\. Is nothing going right anywhere?\.\.
\n<\n[5]>May I ask you to explain just what this "situation" is?\.\.
\n<Ruina>A few nights ago,\. a strange oversurge of Mana shot through the sky and impacted the Fortress.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Indeed.\.\. It was as if a lightning bolt had hit us.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Along with knocking out the power for a while,\. necessitating repairs,\. \BST[1]down in the Mines...\.\.\. something changed.\.\.
Anzu tilts her head as well.\.\.
\n<Ruina>...\.\.\. I suppose there's no harm in you knowing,\. Neneko.\.\.
\n<Ruina>We have something in the Caldera.\.\. \c[18]A Guardian\c[0].\.\. To make sure nothing dangerous or unwanted could use our Lift,\. you see.\.\.
\n<Ruina>It's more impressive and much more tame than a monster,\. I assure you.\.\.
A pained expression crosses the dwarf's face.\.\.

\n<Ruina>They have...\.\.\. for lack of a better term,\. become enraged.\.\. \BST[1]They no longer distinguish between friend or foe,\. dwarf or creature.\.\. They've simply been on a rampage this entire time.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Goodness...\.\.\. That is a very dangerous situation,\. Miss Ruina.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Yes...\.\.\. and if only that were all that's wrong.\.\.
\n<Ruina>I cannot quite explain it...\.\.\. perhaps because you two are not from this Stratum,\. you are less affected by it...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>But there is an...\.\.\. air,\. throughout the entire Stratum.\.\. An oppressive sense of "wrongness".\.\. We have all been feeling it.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Yes...\.\.\. all of my dwarves,\. even I,\. have been growing...\.\.\. restless,\. tense.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Some are having trouble sleeping,\. others have been very anxious and jumpy,\. being a danger to their surroundings.\.\.
\n<Ruina>It seems it is not just those in the Fortress.\.\. The Kobolds have been getting braver and more aggressive.\.\. Monsters wandering in places they shouldn't...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>And down in Mines...\.\.\. our Miners refuse to even enter,\. abandoning work no matter how much incentive,\. or punishment,\. I command.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Yeesh...\.\.\. when you said all that about bad air I was thinking the place just stank or something...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Very much so.\.\. \BST[1]But I digress.\.\. We will handle our own problems.\.\. As for your problem...\.\.\. you can see why I cannot help you.\.\.
The bat sulks...\.\.\. before a thoughtful expression comes to her.\.\. She hums,\. glancing towards Neneko.\.\.
Neneko decides she doesn't like the look Anzu is giving her.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Well,\. I have a solution to at least one of our problems,\. my dear Ruina~\.
Anzu turns,\. an impressively haughty pose as she grins confidently.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>We just happen to be in the same room as the most dependable cat around~\.
\n<\n[5]>Why not have Neneko brave the Caldera to calm down your Guardian?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Why do I have to do it?!\.\.
\n<Ruina>I must agree.\.\. What in particular makes Neneko so capable,\. Lady Anzu?\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Well we have already established that the two of us are the only ones in this fortress unaffected by this...\.\.\. incident.\.\.
Anzu raises a hand to her forehead dramatically.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>And sadly,\. my time above ground has left me...\.\.\. weakened.\.\. I simply do not have the Mana in me to stand against your sacred guardian.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>And besides,\. since I am sure Neneko also wishes to use the Lift and come with me,\. \BST[3]surely she will happily brave this task for all of us!\.\.
Neneko winces,\. knowing that the obnoxious bat was telling the truth.\.\. She needed that Lift.\.\.
The cat turns to Ruina,\. hands on her hips.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>She talks a lot and has a screechy voice but she's right!\.\. I'm dependable as hell,\. Queenie!\.\.
Neneko goes on,\. ignoring Ruina's muttering.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Point me to that Guardian and I'll tame the crap out of it and come back in time for dinner!\.\.
\n<Ruina>...\.\.\. Mm...\.\.\. despite my misgivings,\. I must admit that our options are limited.\.\. Certainly,\. trying cannot hurt.\.\.
Well,\. it could hurt Neneko,\. but the needs of the many,\. and all that.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Very well.\.\. I will send someone to open the way to the Caldera for you.\.\. Good luck,\. Neneko.\.\.
\n<\n[5]>Marvelous~\. Truly,\. it's a nice feeling when such win-\.win deals are made~\. Come along,\. Kitten.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Right,\. right...\.\.\. cuz you're the one doing all the hard work again...\.\.\. grumble grumble
Neneko wearily steps through the footbridge,\. the short guards not sparing a word as they watch her enter.\.\.
For a bunch of shorties,\. all these dwarfs were a lot more stiff than anyone up above ground...\.\.\.
The room she enters is large,\. imposing.\.\. There are guards everywhere.\.\. It makes her fur stand on end.\.\.
But of course,\. what draws her attention the most is the large seat positioned right at the other end of the room.\.\. A literal throne!\.\. What the heck?\.\.

Sitting on the throne is,\. surprise surprise,\. another dwarf.\.\. She had her dark brown hair done up in an admittedly really impressive ponytail,\. and wore a tight white suit that hugged her curves.\.\.
Neneko didn't need to be a genius to figure out she was the top cat around here.\.\.
\n<Guard>Halt!\.\. There is good enough.\.\. Come no closer,\. Beast.\.\.
A blonde,\. short haired,\. surly looking dwarf suddenly moves her weapon in Neneko's path,\. blocking her approach.\.\.
The dwarf leader motions with her hand,\. and the guard flinches slightly,\. lowering her weapon.\.\.
Neneko hesitates,\. not particularly willing to drop it,\. but considering what she came here for and the amount of guards...\.\.\.
The dwarf leader motions with her hand,\. and the guard flinches slightly,\. lowering her weapon.\.\.
She lowers her claws,\. letting some of the tension leak out of her.\.\.
\n<???>I apologize.\.\. It has been a very long time since we've had a new face around here,\. much less a beast kin.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Right...\.\.\. whatever.\.\. So,\. you're the boss around here,\. yeah?\.\.
She nods,\. not put off at all by Neneko's rudeness.\.\.
\n<Ruina>I am Ruina.\.\. I suppose you may call me the Queen of the dwarves.\.\. In truth,\. I primarily oversee the excavating operations of this Stratum.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Essentially,\. nothing happens on this floor without my knowledge.\.\. And if something happens without my permission,\. I make sure it is dealt with.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Perfect!\.\. You're just who I'm looking for,\. then!\.\. Alright,\. listen,\. the name's Neneko,\. and I need your help!\.\.
Ruina raises an eyebrow in curiosity momentarily.\.\.
\n<Ruina>It would depend on what you need help with,\. Neneko.\.\. While you have been friendly with us so far and I've granted you an audience,\. we are very busy with our duties.\.\.
Ruina's eyes widen,\. her brow furrowing.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I know the bastards that did it came through here,\. I know it!\.\. \BST[7]This is the only place they could've gone through!\.\.
She growls,\. glaring up at Ruina with determination.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I'm going to take him back and make the culprits pay.\.\. You just said you know everything about this floor,\. right?\.\.
\n<Ruina>This is a very serious situation Neneko.\.\.
She brings a hand to her chin,\. thinking.\.\.
\n<Ruina>To think they'd do something like this...\.\.\. those foul beasts,\. even going this far...\.\.\.
Neneko jumps,\. only barely stopping herself from pouncing onto Ruina in excitement.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You know who did it!?\.\. Where are they!?\.\.
\n<Ruina>Yes,\. I only know one group who would be cruel enough to do this.\.\.

\n<Ruina>It must be those blasted \c[18]Kobolds\c[0] again.\.\. I thought we'd quelled them after chasing them into their little hive,\. but it seems like they weren't as cornered as we thought...\.\.\.
Neneko thinks about the Kobolds she had encountered before,\. and tries to envision them doing any kind of smuggling or kidnapping.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Hmph.\.\. You underestimate them,\. Neneko.\.\. They are proper pests,\. harassing my dwarves for a while now.\.\.
\n<Ruina>And now they may be disrupting things deeper...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Hang on.\.\. Who are these Kobolds?\.\. You're losing me here!\.\.
\n<Ruina>Yes,\. I suppose you would not be familiar with them.\.\. Little cretins sneaking around in their holes...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Those awful little lizards have been plaguing the First Stratum and making a nuisance of themselves for a while.\.\.
\n<Ruina>They've been interrupting operations here,\. and now they might have gone deeper...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Yes.\.\. They must have snuck past us or found a way into the \c[18]Second Stratum\c[0]...\.\.\. It sounds just like them.\.\.
Neneko recoils with shock.\.\. Second...\.\.\. Stratum...!?\.\.
The Hole...\.\.\. goes even further below!?\.\. But that means...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Now that I think about it,\. Neneko...\.\.\. if I may ask.\.\.
\n<Ruina>I am a bit curious as to how you climbed to the First Stratum.\.\. You definitely did not come through our access.\.\.
The cat scratches her head,\. looking away.\.\. There's...\.\.\. definitely been several misunderstandings here.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Did you sneak past those beasts to use their own tunnels?\.\.
\n<Ruina>...\.\.\. You are not in trouble or anything,\. do not worry.\.\. Although if there are any other ways upward I would appreciate it if you tell me.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Tunnels connecting the Stratums would be a major security concern.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Eheh...\.\.\. right,\. I'll totally keep an eye out.\.\.
It was obvious that they mistook Neneko for a denizen of one of the deeper levels that had climbed up...\.\.\. instead of someone who snuck down.\.\.
And the cat is certainly not eager to correct that mistake.\.\. But now things just got a whole lot more complicated...\.\.\.
She wasn't sure if she could rely on the dwarves or this Queen,\. sitting in her weird fancy throne and working for the Company...\.\.\.
What was with the throne,\. anyway?\.\. They're supposed to be miners or something,\. right?\.\. It feels so flashy and out of place,\. especially...\.\.\.
Neneko focuses on Ruina.\.\. The dwarf in charge.\.\. The so-\.called queen.\.\.
Her hair was pretty.\.\. Long,\. dark,\. cascading down from that jewel studded bangle,\. a slight curl to their tips.\.\. Her bangs also curled,\. framing her face rather nicely.\.\.
Her jumpsuit hugged her figure,\. showing off a rather nice and stocky frame.\.\. Short,\. but definitely packing meat to make up for it.\.\.
She carried herself like a leader,\. that much Neneko could tell.\.\. Her bronze-\.colored eyes were focused and inspired confidence.\.\.
Throughout the conversation the cat could begrudgingly admit that it never felt like Ruina was leading her on.\.\. Everything she said,\. she said with sincerity.\.\.
And not in a condescending way either.\.\. That was kind of nice.\.\. There was business to attend to and she tended to it,\. simple as that.\.\.
Neneko could definitely tell that Ruina took her job seriously.\.\. She kept her cool,\. wasn't overly emotional,\. kept her jumpy underling under control...\.\.\.
Ruina relaxes her shoulders,\. and Neneko blinks,\. twitching her ears as she realizes she must have been staring for a while.\.\.
If the dwarf seemed bothered by the staring she clearly doesn't mention it,\. as she begins speaking again.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Once again,\. I am sorry to hear about your brother,\. Neneko.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Rest assured,\. I have plans for dealing with the kobolds once and for all,\. and now that the possibility has arisen that they may have gotten into trafficking...\.\.\.
\n<Ruina>It may be best to move those plans higher in priority.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Aha...\.\.\. I appreciate it,\. queenie.\.\. Look,\. I...\.\.\.\BST[7] I'm still gonna search around the Stratum.\.\. Just in case.\.\.
\n<Ruina>I will allow this.\.\. Just beware of the dangers outside the walls of this fortress,\. although I am sure someone as capable as you to have snuck your way here can take care of herself.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Heh,\. well if you're gonna point it out yourself~
\n<Ruina>So long as you do not cause any trouble for us,\. you may have limited access to the fortress.\.\.
\n<Ruina>And if you happen upon any concerns or suspicious findings in your search,\. I ask you to bring it to my attention.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Right...\.\.\. yeah,\. don't worry,\. I'm definitely keeping an eye out.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Very well.\.\. I believe that is all for now.\.\.
\^Neneko shifts awkwardly,\. waving a hand before quickly walking out of the room.\|\|
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. Crap,\. dammit...\.\.\. Freaking Hole goes down even deeper...\.\.\. if he's not here then...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I can't tell these shorties I'm not from below.\.\. I dunno how loyal they are to the Company...\.\.\. Means I gotta look around on my own.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Alright,\. Nene,\. just think...\.\.\. Ruina mentioned something about Kobolds and a Hive...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Doubt they actually have anything to do with this,\. but she said they might have a way down...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>It's either that or figure out a way to use the Dwarf's Access somehow...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Tsk.\.\. It's as good a plan as any!\.\. \BST[3]I won't get anything done standing around at least.\.\. Time to get moving!\.\.
Probably the most eye-\.catching thing in the room.\.\. Just above the Queen's head,\. a large,\. sparkling green gem is embedded in the throne.\.\.
It's huge.\.\. The thing must've been the size of Ruina's head.\.\. And...\.\.\. was it glowing?\.\.
Neneko glares at it,\. unaware of the way Ruina had tensed below.\.\.
Neneko's eyes darted between the gem and Ruina,\. who looked...\.\.\. agitated.\.\. Woops,\. probably shouldn't have been eying treasure at the moment...\.\.\.
The cat awkwardly coughs,\. looking away.\.\.
\n<Ruina>While what happened to your brother is a shame and I will have someone look into it later,\. if that is all that needed to be brought to my attention,\. I think this meeting is over.\.\.
\n<Ruina>I am a busy woman,\. beast.\.\. I've extended a bit of hospitality towards you out of kindness,\. but I will not drop everything to cater to you.\.\.
\n<Ruina>Make no mistake,\. I will have order on the Level I am in charge of.\.\. The Kobolds and anything else that upset this floor will be dealt with soon enough.\.\.
\n<Ruina>If that is everything,\. be on your way.\.\. Will you need an escort out?\.\.
Neneko could read the room...\.\.\. she was being kicked out and in a hurry.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>No,\. I'm fine.\.\. I'm heading out to keep looking.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Dammit...\.\.\. what got into her all of a sudden?\.\. She was all polite and business at first and then suddenly started acting like I insulted her mom and spat in her food.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Tch.\.\. Whatever.\.\. I've got bigger problems than a mood swinging shortstack...\.\.\.

\n<\n[1]>Fuck...\.\.\. The Second Stratum...\.\.\. I thought this place would be a whole lotta ground to cover,\. and now there might be an even deeper level...\.\.\. fuck,\. even more for all I know!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Guhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh...\.\.\. Alright Nene,\. you're a tough gal.\.\. No quitting.\.\. There might still be something here.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>And if not...\.\.\. then I'll have to figure out a way even deeper.\.\.
She puts a hand to her chin,\. thinking.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Queenstick in there mentioned the Kobold Hive...\.\.\. If the Dwarves aren't gonna be any help it might be worth checking them out for myself...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>If they don't have a way down,\. then I'll have to get into the Dwarf Access somehow...\.\.\.
Neneko turns around.\.\. The fortress looms over her.\.\. Technically,\. she wasn't banned from entering again,\. although Ruina might not be as welcoming now...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. What was up with that Gem...\.\.\. it felt...\.\.\. funny.\.\. She got all mad when she caught me staring at it...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. Nyaaaaahhh.\.\. It can never just be easy,\. huh?\.\.
\n<Dwarf Axeman>...\.\.\. Can't talk,\. the Queen's here.
\n<Dwarf Lookout>One wrong step,\. catgirl,\. and I'll crank it up!
\n<Ruina>I am Ruina.\.\. I suppose you may call me the Queen of the dwarves.\.\.
\n<Ruina>And I am a busy woman,\. beast.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Oh, it's the shortie again?\.\. \BST[7]She looks as excited as ever...\.\.\.
\n<Lina>Woah!!\.\. Look at the size of those fittings!\.\. So cool!
\n<Lina>At full capacity,\. these babies can carry Mana up to the surface in minutes!\.\. The Fortress is something else!\.\.
\n<Lina>That powerful explosion hit hard,\. though...\.\.\. if we don't repair your little leakage soon...
\n<\n[1]>"Explosion"...?\.\. Could she mean...\.\.\. \BST[6]THAT explosion?!\.\. The one that destroyed the lift?!
\n<Lina>I have to make sure there's not a whiff of Mana escaping from you~...\.\.\. every time it happens there's no way of knowing what will cause up above!
The concerned dwarf voices what's on her mind while working,\. tightening screws and making sure gaskets are in place and in good condition.
\n<Lina>Queen Ruina tried to warn the higher-ups,\. but they're all too busy dealing with what's down below to care about the surface...
\n<Lina>You know...\.\.\. you've caused monsters becoming more aggressive and people of End City getting weird conditions...
\n<Lina>That's why...\.\.\. *HNNG*...\.\.\. I have make sure you're kept shiny and weeeell tightened!
The young redhead,\. completely absorbed in her task and drenched in her own sweat and from the steam coming from the pipes' cooling system,\. doesn't notice the eavesdropping catgirl.
There's calcareous lumps here and there,\. each one vanishing after a grunt of the busy engineer,\. putting her tools to work with force.
\n<Lina>*HRNG*\.\. Who's the bloke who did maintenance last time,\. anyway?!\.\. This is no way to work!
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. and now she's gone full professional at work...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>...\.\.\. whatever.\.\. I should get away before she notices me...
\n<Lina>Forgive my current attire,\. I'm a bit busy right now,\. these pipes won't keep themselves clean without some help from the outside~
\n<Belgrina>You're far from worthy of our trust,\. beast.\.\. You don't belong to this place.
